title: 'I blamed myself for being sexually assaulted'– video
text:
Young minds 'I blamed myself for being sexually assaulted'– video 
In the first of a our three-part series Young Minds, we meet Sheeva, 24, who was sexually assaulted at university. It took her four years of panic attacks, anxiety and depression to accept that she was not blame for what had happened and that she could not have stopped it. She now supports victims of crime, including domestic and sexual violence, through the aftermath of a traumatic event Supported by
